news.title: Madras HC bats for separate sand quarrying department in Tamil Nadu
news.para: However, the state submitted that the authorities had engaged a contractor for excavating and loading the sand in the quarry site and also for transporting the quarried sand to the govt depot.

news.title: Kanpur development body completes survey to develop township in Bingawan
news.para: A survey for the township to be developed in 60 hectares in Bingawan has already been completed. For the proposed township 24 hectares of land will be purchased while the remaining land belongs to KDA.

news.title: Sunteck Realty lease out its building in Mumbai for 29 years
news.para: The built‐up area of Sunteck Icon is approximately two lakh sq ft with an approximate rental of Rs 300 per sq ft per month on carpet area basis. This will allow Sunteck Realty to generate a revenue of close to Rs 2,000 crore over the tenure of 29 years.

news.title: China Vanke's shares drop by 12% after disappointing earnings
news.para: The Hong Kong stock of China's second-largest developer by sales touched a low of HK$4.77. Its shares in Shenzhen, which continued trading during Hong Kong's holidays on Friday and Monday, dropped 5.2% on Tuesday to 8.51 yuan, the lowest since July 2014.

news.title: Indore halts collector’s guidelines; losses may run in crores
news.para: The same was set to be implemented from April 1 to help generate around Rs 2,700 crore of revenue by Indore stamp and registrar department in 2024-25.

news.title: Sobha to execute a project on 2.03 acre land in Gurugram
news.para: With this acquisition, Sobha plans to execute a project in approximately 2.03125 acres of land situated at sector 106, Gurugram.

news.title: Homes prices in UK rise by 1.6% in March
news.para: Nationwide Building Society, Britain's second-largest mortgage lender, said house prices were 1.6% higher in March from a year earlier at an average of 261,142 pounds ($328,229), picking up from annual growth of 1.2% in February.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects property tax worth Rs 206 crore in FY24
news.para: For the 2022-23 fiscal, the property tax collection figure of the civic body was Rs 188 crore. The NMC had set a property tax collection target of Rs 210 crore for the 2023-24 financial year that just concluded.

news.title: Lucknow development body sold properties worth Rs 2,629 crore in FY24
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Indramani Tripathi attributed this success to the e-auction initiative. Commercial and residential properties valued at Rs 2,058.64 crore were successfully auctioned online.

news.title: Rajkot civic body collects property tax worth Rs 365.49 crore in FY24
news.para: This has made the tax income of RMC rise by more than 90% over the last five financial years — from Rs 189.58 crore in 2019-20 to Rs 365.49 crore in 2023-24.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body collects property tax worth Rs 977 crore in FY24
news.para: Civic officials said the municipal corporation earned Rs977 crore revenue through property tax this fiscal, compared to Rs810 crore collected in 2022-23 and Rs628 crore in 2021-22.

news.title: Halted drive in merged areas hits Pune civic body's property tax earnings in FY24
news.para: Property tax is usually the largest source of revenue for Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC). Around Rs2,268 crore was earned from it in the latest fiscal, states official data.

news.title: Lucknow civic body collects property tax worth over Rs 650 crore in FY24
news.para: The achievement was driven by a remarkable increase of over 26% in property and house tax collection, soaring from Rs 338 crore to Rs 425 crore compared to the previous fiscal year.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body collects property tax worth Rs 457.2 crore in FY24
news.para: GVMC leads in tax collections despite cities falling short of targets. Traders delay payments for election funding. GMC commissioner notes uncollectible amount affecting revenue.

news.title: Lucknow civic body launches campaign to update KYC record
news.para: The LMC employeeswill update the mobile numbers and other missing records of the property owners. This will help the corporation to coordinate with customers and provide various details of schemes, taxes, and other information by the LMC.

news.title: Mumbai: 27-acre railway land handed over for Dharavi redevelopment
news.para: Dharavi project progresses with 27.6 acres acquired for modern housing and facilities. The Adani Group to invest Rs 5,069 crore in redeveloping Dharavi, aiming for completion within three years of commencement.

news.title: With 10% hike in circle rates, land prices in Jaipur escalates
news.para: At present, the highest district level committee (DLC) rate in Jaipur is for C-Scheme and MI Road areas, where per square feet costs range between Rs 90,000 and Rs 1.25 lakh.

news.title: Maharashtra's IGR department earns Rs 50,143 crore in FY24
news.para: The registration of property with inspector general of registration (IGR) department was a key contributor to the state exchequer.

news.title: Apartments in Bengaluru not finding tankers to sell treated water
news.para: Bengaluru apartments sell treated water, facing tanker shortage. Rajagopalan R sells from 5 blocks daily. Tankers can't supply drinking water. BAF vice-president struggles. Credai partnership for treated water revenue with BWSSB supply starting soon.
